# Cline rules for Baby Pulmo

You are working on Baby Pulmo — WhatsApp-native AI for pediatric pneumonia screening in rural Bangladesh (Next.js 14 + Supabase + Modal + GCP TTS + Wav2Vec2).

## Memory Bank

At the start of every task, read all files in `memory-bank/`:
- `projectbrief.md` — what Baby Pulmo is, who for, success criteria.
- `productContext.md` — the problem, why this stack, regulatory framing.
- `systemPatterns.md` — architecture + §3 LLM carve-out + override precedence.
- `techContext.md` — stack, build commands, deploy.
- `activeContext.md` — what's in flight right now.
- `progress.md` — phase status.

After reading the Memory Bank, also read `CLAUDE.md` and `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the canonical context.

## Non-negotiable rule

**Never add a runtime LLM call in the caregiver-facing path.** Severity is deterministic (`lib/claude.ts::decideSeverityMultiModal`). Bangla audio is clinician-vetted stock library (`lib/tts.ts::STOCK_BANGLA`). LLMs ARE allowed in the §3 ARCHITECTURE.md carve-out boundaries only (build-time, one-shot ingest, CHW-side, partner MCP, federated, CXR vision).

## File-path discipline

Every claim cites a file path. `grep` to confirm before claiming.

## Style

TypeScript strict, no `any`. Tailwind only. Prefer existing helpers in `lib/`. Update `.env.example` whenever introducing a new env var.
